That said, I think the get_blob() behavior is wrong. Using it can result in a NOT_FOUND error in cases where a resource of the input name is always available.

Retrying 2-3 times automatically to achieve consistency, or else failing completely with a CONFLICT or a custom error, would be significantly better behavior than failing with a NOT_FOUND error in a scenario where there is always a resource with the input name available. NOT_FOUND is surprising and leads the user on a wild goose chase looking for deleted objects.

