You could create a decorator that users could use wherever they want. For instance, in client code they could do something like this:

```
from nupic.encoders import SomeEncoder
from nupic.utils import cache

class CachedSomeEncoder(SomeEncoder):
  @cache(size=1000)
  def encode(self, value):
    super(self, CachedSomeEncoder).encode(value)
```

This keeps the opinion of whether caching should be done out of the core implementations and gives users flexibility to apply caching to any deterministic functions they want.

