@indirectlylit I believe we should merge it.

Because of the long break, I am sort of loosing track of what was the accepted support for 0.7.x, stuff we already fixed in relation to path and C extension issues -- but I believe that we accepted that not all Ubuntu platforms (like 14.04) would be supported.

I also think we switched off SSL in 0.7.x, and I don't think we should backport this in order to re-introduce SSL, given the additional amount of testing and further unclarity. I think, if people are already running a 0.7 release, they would expect their platforms to continue to be supported, and we shouldn't worry too much about additional platform support since 0.8 isn't too far (especially not if we mean the first pre-releases).
